The Professional Wrestling Federation was created by Italian Stallion and George South in the late 80's. This is the story of two journeymen who created their own territory in the days of mainstream professional wrestling. The stars of the PWF not only competed on the indie circuit but they were also known as the "jobber crew" for WCW and WWF.The PWF was surrounded by controversy for "Booking Fees' and the stigma of PWF standing for "Please Wrestle Free". The PWF was known for creating stars such as Henry Godwinn, R-Truth, Men on a Mission, Charles Robinson, and many other great wrestling stars.Learn of the impact the PWF had on the early stages of indie wrestling from the wrestlers and owners. This 2 disc set is loaded with over 8 hours of PWF matches, stories, and feature length documentary.DISC 1
